The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Monday, June 07, 2004 				 Parched hospital
Krishnagar (Nadia), June 6: More than 400 patients at Jawaharlal Nehru Memorial Hospital in Kalyani are thirsting for water since the only reservoir atop the building and the water pipes developed cracks after being struck by lightning on Thursday.																								The ruptures on the walls of the tank were detected on Friday. The cracks were on its upper portion and during the early part of the day, did not affect supply. When we tried to fill it up, the pipes were leaking, hospital superintendent Nirupam Biswas said.																								He added that the public health engineering department was informed immediately but Kalyani municipality chairman Shantanu Jha said he came to know about the crisis this morning.
